<div class=3D"staticpageheader"><h1 class=3D"staticpagetitle">Effective Fie=
ld Goal Percentage Calculator</h1>
<div class=3D"staticpageauthor"><br>
</div></div>
<p>The effective field goal percentage is a statistic used in basketball to=
 take into consideration the additional difficulty of three-point shots and=
 the extra points awarded for making a three-pointer.</p>

<p>Effective Field Goal Percentage, or eFG%, is calculated the following wa=
y:</p>

<p><strong>(2pt FGM + 1.5 * 3pt FGM) / FGA</strong></p>

<p>Where:=20
	</p><ul>
    	<li><strong>2 pt FGM</strong> =3D 2 points Field Goal Made</li>
        <li><strong>3 pt FGM</strong> =3D 3 points Field Goal Made</li>
        <li><strong>FGA</strong> =3D Field Goal Attempts</li>
    </ul>
<p></p>




